DAT
id=qid::label=str::text=lstr::
5102::$$$message_0045_0000_0000$$$::As soon as I leave, the weight on my shoulders seems to lift.[lr]::
5103::$$$message_0045_0000_0001$$$::It might be because I'm away from the priest.[lr]::
5104::$$$message_0045_0000_0002$$$::But it might also be because I see Tohsaka, conspicuous in her uniform,[lr]::
5105::$$$message_0045_0000_0003$$$::and the blonde girl in a raincoat. The slightly mismatched sight of those two standing together relieves whatever pressure I felt.::
5106::$$$message_0045_0001_0000$$$::[font italic=true]...[font italic=false][lr]::
5107::$$$message_0045_0001_0001$$$::Saber is still silent.[lr]::
5108::$$$message_0045_0001_0002$$$::She looks at me, and seems to want to know what I decided.::
5109::$$$message_0045_0002_0000$$$::"Let's go. We're going in the same direction until we reach town."[lr]::
5110::$$$message_0045_0002_0001$$$::Tohsaka starts walking, her pace brisk.[lr]::
5111::$$$message_0045_0002_0002$$$::Saber and I follow suit, and the three of us leave the church grounds.::
5112::$$$message_0045_0003_0000$$$::We walk down the hill.[lr]::
5113::$$$message_0045_0003_0001$$$::We hadn't talked much on the way here, but there's even less conversation on the way back.[lr]::
5114::$$$message_0045_0003_0002$$$::Even someone as dull as me knows why.[lr]::
5115::$$$message_0045_0003_0003$$$::After our visit to the church, I accepted my position as a Master.[lr]::
5116::$$$message_0045_0003_0004$$$::That must be why Tohsaka is keeping her distance.::
5117::$$$message_0045_0004_0000$$$::[font italic=true]...[font italic=false][lr]::
5118::$$$message_0045_0004_0001$$$::I get it.[lr]::
5119::$$$message_0045_0004_0002$$$::But I don't like the idea of seeing Tohsaka in that light.::
5120::$$$message_0045_0005_0000$$$::"Tohsaka. How's your Servant?"[lr]::
5121::$$$message_0045_0005_0001$$$::"Eh?"[lr]::
5122::$$$message_0045_0005_0002$$$::"Oh. If you're wondering, Archer's fine. The injury he sustained from Saber won't be easy to heal, so he won't materialize for a while though."[lr]::
5123::$$$message_0045_0005_0003$$$::"Does that mean he isn't by your side?"::
5124::$$$message_0045_0006_0000$$$::"Nope. He's cooped up in my house. He'd be at a disadvantage if he was ambushed by other Servants, so I'm having him prepare to fight by recuperating somewhere safe."::
5125::$$$message_0045_0007_0000$$$::I see.[lr]::
5126::$$$message_0045_0007_0001$$$::Unlike my house, I'm sure Tohsaka's house is well-fortified against enemies.::
5127::$$$message_0045_0008_0000$$$::A mage's home is like a fortress. There's not much chance of defeating them there.[lr]::
5128::$$$message_0045_0008_0001$$$::Which means enemies tend not to try attacking them at home.[lr]::
5129::$$$message_0045_0008_0002$$$::Hm...[lr]::
5130::$$$message_0045_0008_0003$$$::The Bounded Field around our house just notifies us of intruders, but even having that makes a big difference.::
5131::$$$message_0045_0009_0000$$$::"By the way, Tohsaka. The priest mentioned he was the overseer of the Holy Grail War. Does that mean he knows who your Servant is?"[lr]::
5132::$$$message_0045_0009_0001$$$::"He shouldn't know. I've never told him."::
5133::$$$message_0045_0010_0000$$$::"I see. You guys seem to get along, so I thought you had."[lr]::
5134::$$$message_0045_0010_0001$$$::"Emiya. I'm going to give you a little advice. Never tell anybody your Servant's identity. No matter how much you trust the other person, you should keep quiet. Otherwise, you'll end up dropping out early."::
5135::$$$message_0045_0011_0000$$$::"Huh? What do you mean, Saber's identity?"[lr]::
5136::$$$message_0045_0011_0001$$$::"I'm talking about which hero your Servant is.[lr]::
5137::$$$message_0045_0011_0002$$$::No matter how strong they are, revealing their strength to others will just lead to a knife in the back. Just ask Saber her True Name later.[lr]::
5138::$$$message_0045_0011_0003$$$::You'll understand when you learn about her. Actually... It might be better if she doesn't tell you because you're...you know..."::
5139::$$$message_0045_0012_0000$$$::"Why not?"[lr]::
5140::$$$message_0045_0012_0001$$$::"You can't keep secrets. You might have the best chance at keeping the secret if you just don't know."[lr]::
5141::$$$message_0045_0012_0002$$$::"Who do you think I am? I can at least follow a strategy like that."::
5142::$$$message_0045_0013_0000$$$::"Are you sure? Does that mean there's something you're hiding from me?"[lr]::
5143::$$$message_0045_0013_0001$$$::"Uh...something I'm hiding from you? Well..."[lr]::
5144::$$$message_0045_0013_0002$$$::I feel a hot blush in my cheeks as she looks at me.[lr]::
5145::$$$message_0045_0013_0003$$$::I shouldn't feel guilty, but I wonder if secretly idolizing her even counts in this context.::
5146::$$$message_0045_0014_0000$$$::"See? I don't know what it is, but your face tells me you're hiding something. And that's why you're not fit for this.[lr]::
5147::$$$message_0045_0014_0001$$$::There's plenty of other good things about you, so stop thinking of silly tactics like these."::
5148::$$$message_0045_0015_0000$$$::"Uh-huh. Then what about you? If you're mum about your Servant even to that priest, does that mean you don't trust him?"::
5149::$$$message_0045_0016_0000$$$::"Kirei? Of course not. I'm not naĂŻve enough to trust him. He's a big hypocrite who switched sides from the Church to the Mage's Association, yet he still has a seat at the Church. He'd spill it to the other Masters the second he felt like it."::
5150::$$$message_0045_0017_0000$$$::Tohsaka huffs, obviously annoyed.[lr]::
5151::$$$message_0045_0017_0001$$$::I guess Tohsaka really doesn't trust that priest.[lr]::
5152::$$$message_0045_0017_0002$$$::I'm a little relieved. But at the same time, her tone of voice also conveys a sort of closeness with the priest.::
5153::$$$message_0045_0018_0000$$$::We cross the bridge.[lr]::
5154::$$$message_0045_0018_0001$$$::There's nothing else to talk about.[lr]::
5155::$$$message_0045_0018_0002$$$::Our frosty white breath hangs in the winter air.[lr]::
5156::$$$message_0045_0018_0003$$$::The faint sound of flowing water bubbles up from beneath the bridge where we walk in the streetlights' illumination.[lr]::
5157::$$$message_0045_0018_0004$$$::All of those small details etch themselves onto my memory.::
5158::$$$message_0045_0019_0000$$$::Oddly, I don't think to look at Tohsaka's face.[lr]::
5159::$$$message_0045_0019_0001$$$::It feels like more of a rarity to be walking beside her like this than it does to see her face.[lr]::
5160::$$$message_0045_0019_0002$$$::Me, Tohsaka, and the girl called Saber, about whom I know nothing...[lr]::
5161::$$$message_0045_0019_0003$$$::The three us, without doing anything in particular, walk back to our homes.::
5162::$$$message_0045_0020_0000$$$::We reach the intersection.[lr]::
5163::$$$message_0045_0020_0001$$$::It is where we will have to separate, as our homes are in opposite directions.::
5164::$$$message_0045_0021_0000$$$::"We should split up here. I've done my duty, and things would get complicated if we stuck together any longer. We should part ways amicably, and tomorrow we'll become enemies."[lr]::
5165::$$$message_0045_0021_0001$$$::I think she's trying to bring closure to our ambiguous relationship.[lr]::
5166::$$$message_0045_0021_0002$$$::Tohsaka starts talking, but suddenly cuts off.::
5167::$$$message_0045_0022_0000$$$::Then I realize something.[lr]::
5168::$$$message_0045_0022_0001$$$::She didn't explain the rules to me out of obligation.[lr]::
5169::$$$message_0045_0022_0002$$$::She was only trying to help me, as I knew absolutely nothing, to make things fair for me.[lr]::
5170::$$$message_0045_0022_0003$$$::And that's why, the moment things have been explained, everything goes back to normal.[lr]::
5171::$$$message_0045_0022_0004$$$::All that's left is for us to fight each other as Masters.::
5172::$$$message_0045_0023_0000$$$::"Hm?"[lr]::
5173::$$$message_0045_0023_0001$$$::But that would make her last words to me strange.[lr]::
5174::$$$message_0045_0023_0002$$$::Tohsaka must have meant it would be hard to fight if she feels empathy for me.[lr]::
5175::$$$message_0045_0023_0003$$$::For Tohsaka, everything that happened tonight was unnecessary.[lr]::
5176::$$$message_0045_0023_0004$$$::[font italic=true]"...things would get complicated if we stuck together any longer."[font italic=false][r]::
5177::$$$message_0045_0023_0005$$$::If that's how she feels, she shouldn't have gotten involved with me to begin with.::
5178::$$$message_0045_0024_0000$$$::She's smart enough to know that.[lr]::
5179::$$$message_0045_0024_0001$$$::But she helped me, even knowing it wouldn't benefit her in any way.::
5180::$$$message_0045_0025_0000$$$::That's how I know she had had no ulterior motive for doing what she did tonight... She did it purely out of the kindness of her heart.[lr]::
5181::$$$message_0045_0025_0001$$$::Tohsaka is totally different now than she usually is at school.[lr]::
5182::$$$message_0045_0025_0002$$$::She's harsh and unfriendly at school, and that's putting it mildly. But seeing her right now? I want to ask why the hell she acts the way she does at school.::
5183::$$$message_0045_0026_0000$$$::Honestly? The difference is on the level of fraud.[lr]::
5184::$$$message_0045_0026_0001$$$::But either way...[lr]::
5185::$$$message_0045_0026_0002$$$::Rin Tohsaka is also exactly what everyone thinks she is.::
5186::$$$message_0045_0027_0000$$$::"You know. You're a good person, Tohsaka."[lr]::
5187::$$$message_0045_0027_0001$$$::"Huh? Where'd that come from? Flattery won't make me go easy on you."[lr]::
5188::$$$message_0045_0027_0002$$$::I know that.[lr]::
5189::$$$message_0045_0027_0003$$$::She had to tell me it would be a pain to be empathetic BECAUSE she isn't going to go easy on me.::
5190::$$$message_0045_0028_0000$$$::"I know. But I would rather not be enemies with you, because I like people like you."[lr]::
5191::$$$message_0045_0028_0001$$$::"Wha..."::
5192::$$$message_0045_0029_0000$$$::I heard Tohsaka's house is in the residential district with all the Western houses, in the opposite direction of my house.[lr]::
5193::$$$message_0045_0029_0001$$$::She took care of me up until now, so I'd like to walk her home.::
5194::$$$message_0045_0030_0000$$$::"A-anyway, don't forget to run to that church the moment your Servant is killed. You'll at least live if you do that."[lr]::
5195::$$$message_0045_0030_0001$$$::"I'm not sure about that, but I'll still take your advice. Anyway, I don't think that will happen, since I'm likely to die before Saber." ::
5196::$$$message_0045_0031_0000$$$::I've calmly assessed the situation.[lr]::
5197::$$$message_0045_0031_0001$$$::"Hnn..."[lr]::
5198::$$$message_0045_0031_0002$$$::Tohsaka's reaction is once again puzzling.[lr]::
5199::$$$message_0045_0031_0003$$$::After that weary sigh, she glances at Saber.::
5200::$$$message_0045_0032_0000$$$::"Fine. I won't warn you anymore. At this point, it would really just be an act of empathy.[lr]::
5201::$$$message_0045_0032_0001$$$::Just be careful. Saber may be strong, but it's all over if you, the Master, wind up dead."[lr]::
5202::$$$message_0045_0032_0002$$$::She turns around and starts walking.::
5203::$$$message_0045_0033_0000$$$::[font italic=true]...[font italic=false][lr]::
5204::$$$message_0045_0033_0001$$$::And yet...[lr]::
5205::$$$message_0045_0033_0002$$$::She stops dead in her tracks, as if she's seen a ghost.::
5206::$$$message_0045_0034_0000$$$::"Tohsaka?"[lr]::
5207::$$$message_0045_0034_0001$$$::The moment I call out to her, a stinging pain shoots through my left hand.::
5208::$$$message_0045_0035_0000$$$::                                       â€śAre you two done chatting?â€ť::
5209::$$$message_0045_0036_0000$$$::A young voice echoes in the night.[lr]::
5210::$$$message_0045_0036_0001$$$::The singsong tone comes unmistakably from a young girl.[lr]::
5211::$$$message_0045_0036_0002$$$::My eyes are drawn to the top of the hill.[lr]::
5212::$$$message_0045_0036_0003$$$::I hadn't noticed the clouds parting. Now the brilliant moon illuminates the sky.[lr]::
5213::$$$message_0045_0036_0004$$$::And there...::
5214::$$$message_0045_0037_0000$$$::...a shadow looms.[lr]::
5215::$$$message_0045_0037_0001$$$::It's a strange shape that seems out of place in the darkened town.::
5216::$$$message_0045_0038_0000$$$::"Berserker."[lr]::
5217::$$$message_0045_0038_0001$$$::I'm not familiar with the word Tohsaka whispers.[lr]::
5218::$$$message_0045_0038_0002$$$::I don't even need to ask.[lr]::
5219::$$$message_0045_0038_0003$$$::It's definitely a Servant.[lr]::
5220::$$$message_0045_0038_0004$$$::It gives off an overwhelming aura of death that surpasses even the fire from ten years ago.::
5221::$$$message_0045_0039_0000$$$::"Good evening, brother. This is the second time we've met."[lr]::
5222::$$$message_0045_0039_0001$$$::The girl smiles.[lr]::
5223::$$$message_0045_0039_0002$$$::Her innocence sends a chill up my spine.::
5224::$$$message_0045_0040_0000$$$::[font italic=true]...[font italic=false][lr]::
5225::$$$message_0045_0040_0001$$$::No, the chill goes deeper than that.[lr]::
5226::$$$message_0045_0040_0002$$$::It's not just my body. Even my mind freezes.[lr]::
5227::$$$message_0045_0040_0003$$$::That thing is a monster.[lr]::
5228::$$$message_0045_0040_0004$$$::I'm not even looking into its eyes, but its intimidating presence paralyzes me.::
5229::$$$message_0045_0041_0000$$$::My instincts tell me I'm dead the instant I move.[lr]::
5230::$$$message_0045_0041_0001$$$::It feels like someone is pressing a knife against my exposed stomach.::
5231::$$$message_0045_0042_0000$$$::"Crap. He's definitely in a different league."[lr]::
5232::$$$message_0045_0042_0001$$$::While all I manage to do is stand there, paralyzed, Tohsaka is composed enough to brace herself.[lr]::
5233::$$$message_0045_0042_0002$$$::Even that seems futile.[lr]::
5234::$$$message_0045_0042_0003$$$::I can only see her back, but I still sense her despair.::
5235::$$$message_0045_0042_0004$$$::"Huh? Oh, your Servant's resting. That's no fun. I thought I would get rid of two at once."::
5236::$$$message_0045_0042_0005$$$::The young girl seems displeased as she stands at the top of the hill looking down on us.[lr]::
5237::$$$message_0045_0042_0006$$$::This is even worse.[lr]::
5238::$$$message_0045_0042_0007$$$::That girl knows that Tohsaka's Servant is not here.::
5239::$$$message_0045_0042_0008$$$::And then...[lr]::
5240::$$$message_0045_0042_0009$$$::The girl bows gracefully, which seems wildly out of place given the current mood.::
5241::$$$message_0045_0042_0010$$$::"Very nice to meet you, Rin. My name is Illya.[lr]::
5242::$$$message_0045_0042_0011$$$::Perhaps you might recognize the name Illyasviel von Einzbern better."[lr]::
5243::$$$message_0045_0042_0012$$$::"Einzbern..."[lr]::
5244::$$$message_0045_0042_0013$$$::Tohsaka trembles lightly, seeming to recognize the name.::
5245::$$$message_0045_0042_0014$$$::The girl smiles, seemingly delighted by Tohsaka's reaction.[lr]::
5246::$$$message_0045_0042_0015$$$::"Then here we go. Kill them, Berserker."[lr]::
5247::$$$message_0045_0042_0016$$$::In a singsong voice, the girl orders the monstrosity behind her.::
5248::$$$message_0045_0042_0017$$$::The giant jumps.[lr]::
5249::$$$message_0045_0042_0018$$$::In a single leap, this Berserker sails all the way from the top of the hill to its bottom, where we stand.::
5250::$$$message_0045_0042_0019$$$::"Shirou, get back!"[lr]::
5251::$$$message_0045_0042_0020$$$::Saber surges forward. Her raincoat flutters off her shoulders, blocking my view for a moment.::
5252::$$$message_0045_0042_0021$$$::Saber runs towards where Berserker is about to land.[lr]::
5253::$$$message_0045_0042_0022$$$::Berserker lands, kicking up a small torrent of air in his wake. The two meet almost simultaneously.::
5254::$$$message_0045_0042_0023$$$::"...!"[lr]::
5255::$$$message_0045_0042_0024$$$::The very [font italic=true]air[font italic=false] shakes.[lr]::
5256::$$$message_0045_0042_0025$$$::Saber stops Berserker's rocklike sword with her invisible sword.::
5257::$$$message_0045_0042_0026$$$::"...ng!"[lr]::
5258::$$$message_0045_0042_0027$$$::Saber's mouth twists as she strains.[lr]::
5259::$$$message_0045_0042_0028$$$::And then...[r]::
5260::$$$message_0045_0042_0029$$$::Berserker's giant sword moves in a flash, creating a whirlwind.::
5261::$$$message_0045_0042_0030$$$::Thunder.[lr]::
5262::$$$message_0045_0042_0031$$$::The clash of swords, almost tearing the air, ends in Saber's defeat.::
5263::$$$message_0045_0042_0032$$$::I hear something skidding.[lr]::
5264::$$$message_0045_0042_0033$$$::Saber blocks Berserker's giant sword with her own, but the impact pushes her backwards.::
5265::$$$message_0045_0042_0034$$$::"Gngh!"[lr]::
5266::$$$message_0045_0042_0035$$$::Saber buckles.[lr]::
5267::$$$message_0045_0042_0036$$$::The copper-skinned Servant follows her.[lr]::
5268::$$$message_0045_0042_0037$$$::The monster swings its giant sword again and again, as if it knows how to do nothing else.::
5269::$$$message_0045_0042_0038$$$::Saber continues to block it with her sword, unable to dodge the strikes.[lr]::
5270::$$$message_0045_0042_0039$$$::Saber's sword being invisible doesn't matter.[lr]::
5271::$$$message_0045_0042_0040$$$::She needs to put all her strength into blocking his attacks, or she's dead for sure.::
5272::$$$message_0045_0042_0041$$$::Saber's left with no choice but to remain on the defensive.[lr]::
5273::$$$message_0045_0042_0042$$$::The only chance Saber has of winning is to find an opportunity to strike between Berserker's attacks.[lr]::
5274::$$$message_0045_0042_0043$$$::And yet...[lr]::
5275::$$$message_0045_0042_0044$$$::That's only if Berserker leaves her an opening.::
5276::$$$message_0045_0042_0045$$$::His massive black rock sword moves like a raging storm.[lr]::
5277::$$$message_0045_0042_0046$$$::He is [font italic=true]enormous.[font italic=false][lr]::
5278::$$$message_0045_0042_0047$$$::Despite his size and unwieldy weapon, Berserker is faster than Saber.::
5279::$$$message_0045_0042_0048$$$::His unrelenting attacks just smash whatever is in his way. That's all.::
5280::$$$message_0045_0042_0049$$$::But it's enough to be effective.[lr]::
5281::$$$message_0045_0042_0050$$$::As long as he retains his overwhelming speed and power, he doesn't really need technique.[lr]::
5282::$$$message_0045_0042_0051$$$::Humans devised technique to compensate for their own weakness.[lr]::
5283::$$$message_0045_0042_0052$$$::That giant? That monster? He has no weakness.::
5284::$$$message_0045_0042_0053$$$::"Run!"[lr]::
5285::$$$message_0045_0042_0054$$$::It's the only thing I can manage to say. My body is completely frozen.[lr]::
5286::$$$message_0045_0042_0055$$$::That thing cannot be beaten.[lr]::
5287::$$$message_0045_0042_0056$$$::Saber is going to die.[lr]::
5288::$$$message_0045_0042_0057$$$::That's why she needs to run.[lr]::
5289::$$$message_0045_0042_0058$$$::It'd be easy if it was just her that needed to flee.[lr]::
5290::$$$message_0045_0042_0059$$$::Of course, she knows that perfectly well.::
5291::$$$message_0045_0042_0060$$$::"Oh..."[lr]::
5292::$$$message_0045_0042_0061$$$::That's not good.[lr]::
5293::$$$message_0045_0042_0062$$$::My body may be paralyzed, but my mind is still working.[lr]::
5294::$$$message_0045_0042_0063$$$::The raging storm of death simply won't let up.[lr]::
5295::$$$message_0045_0042_0064$$$::Saber retreats, unable to block it all.[lr]::
5296::$$$message_0045_0042_0065$$$::And then, the final unblockable blow comes.::
5297::$$$message_0045_0043_0000$$$::Saber hangs in the air.[lr]::
5298::$$$message_0045_0043_0001$$$::Twisting her body impossibly, Saber manages to defend against Berserker's titanic swing.::
5299::$$$message_0045_0044_0000$$$::It's all she can do to defend herself from the fatal blow.[lr]::
5300::$$$message_0045_0044_0001$$$::But because she can't completely brace against the giant's tremendous swing, his attack sends her flying.::
5301::$$$message_0045_0045_0000$$$::After sailing in a wide arc, she falls to the ground.[lr]::
5302::$$$message_0045_0045_0001$$$::Just before her back hits the ground, Saber turns in midair and lands on her feet.[lr]::
5303::$$$message_0045_0045_0002$$$::"...Ungh!"[lr]::
5304::$$$message_0045_0045_0003$$$::She manages to compose herself.[lr]::
5305::$$$message_0045_0045_0004$$$::But crimson blood stains her chest.::
5306::$$$message_0045_0045_0005$$$::"She...!"[lr]::
5307::$$$message_0045_0045_0006$$$::I'm such an idiot.[lr]::
5308::$$$message_0045_0045_0007$$$::I've completely forgotten something crucial.[lr]::
5309::$$$message_0045_0045_0008$$$::I don't know how many times Servants can fight in a day, but this is Saber's third battle.[lr]::
5310::$$$message_0045_0045_0009$$$::On top of that, Saber still hasn't healed from the wound Lancer inflicted on her chest earlier.::
5311::$$$message_0045_0045_0010$$$::"Ungh...gh..."[lr]::
5312::$$$message_0045_0045_0011$$$::Saber shifts her guard to protect her chest.[lr]::
5313::$$$message_0045_0045_0012$$$::Berserker moves in, like a violent wind, striking at Saber while she's hampered by her wound.[lr]::
5314::$$$message_0045_0045_0013$$$::His blows rain down on her back.::
5315::$$$message_0045_0045_0014$$$::"Vier Stil ErschieĂźung...!"[lr]::
5316::$$$message_0045_0045_0015$$$::I don't know what kind of magecraft Tohsaka used, but something bursts against Berserker's body.[lr]::
5317::$$$message_0045_0045_0016$$$::From the amount of magical energy I can feel, the impact must have been equivalent to a large caliber pistol.::
5318::$$$message_0045_0045_0017$$$::Even that is meaningless.[lr]::
5319::$$$message_0045_0045_0018$$$::It barely even scratches him.[lr]::
5320::$$$message_0045_0045_0019$$$::He isn't nullifying magical energy, like what Saber does.[lr]::
5321::$$$message_0045_0045_0020$$$::The attack just...doesn't affect him.::
5322::$$$message_0045_0045_0021$$$::"What!? This guy is ridiculously durable!!!"[lr]::
5323::$$$message_0045_0045_0022$$$::Despite that, Tohsaka continues to cast her spell.[lr]::
5324::$$$message_0045_0045_0023$$$::Berserker just ignores Tohsaka's spells and charges at Saber.::
5325::$$$message_0045_0045_0024$$$::"...Nngh!"[lr]::
5326::$$$message_0045_0045_0025$$$::Saber painfully lifts her head.[lr]::
5327::$$$message_0045_0045_0026$$$::She readies her sword, intent on continuing the fight.[lr]::
5328::$$$message_0045_0045_0027$$$::The sight of her in so much pain gets me moving again.::
5329::$$$message_0045_0046_0000$$$::"No! Run, Saber!"[lr]::
5330::$$$message_0045_0046_0001$$$::I yell with all my might.[lr]::
5331::$$$message_0045_0046_0002$$$::She hears me.::
5332::$$$message_0045_0046_0003$$$::But she braces herself to confront an enemy she can't possibly compete with.::
5333::$$$message_0045_0046_0004$$$::Berserker's attacks are relentless.[lr]::
5334::$$$message_0045_0046_0005$$$::Saber weakens with every block. The end slowly creeps up on her.[lr]::
5335::$$$message_0045_0046_0006$$$::Where in that small frame of hers does such power come from?::
5336::$$$message_0045_0046_0007$$$::Saber doesn't retreat.[lr]::
5337::$$$message_0045_0046_0008$$$::She endures the great sword's furious attacks, and tries to push Berserker back with sheer vigor.[lr]::
5338::$$$message_0045_0046_0009$$$::She has no chance of winning.[lr]::
5339::$$$message_0045_0046_0010$$$::Even though she knows her demise is inevitable, she holds her ground adamantly.::
5340::$$$message_0045_0046_0011$$$::Maybe it sensed something from her.[lr]::
5341::$$$message_0045_0046_0012$$$::"[wacky len=12]!!!"[lr]::
5342::$$$message_0045_0046_0013$$$::The monster, silent until now, suddenly roars.::
5343::$$$message_0045_0046_0014$$$::Its attacks are impossible to block.[lr]::
5344::$$$message_0045_0046_0015$$$::Its attacks rain down on her, though her defense is flawless. But one strike finally sends her flying.[lr]::
5345::$$$message_0045_0046_0016$$$::[font italic=true]Slam![font italic=false][lr]::
5346::$$$message_0045_0046_0017$$$::It's the sound of something falling in the distance.::
5347::$$$message_0045_0046_0018$$$::Fresh blood stains her armor.[lr]::
5348::$$$message_0045_0046_0019$$$::Her small frame shouldn't be able to rise. And yet...[lr]::
5349::$$$message_0045_0046_0020$$$::"No..."[lr]::
5350::$$$message_0045_0046_0021$$$::She stands up without thinking.[lr]::
5351::$$$message_0045_0046_0022$$$::Her actions say that she needs to keep going, or else I'll be killed.::
5352::$$$message_0045_0046_0023$$$::"..."[lr]::
5353::$$$message_0045_0046_0024$$$::Her actions...[lr]::
5354::$$$message_0045_0046_0025$$$::I realize I made a foolish decision.::
5355::$$$message_0045_0046_0026$$$::Berserker stops after defeating Saber.[lr]::
5356::$$$message_0045_0046_0027$$$::It doesn't so much as look at Tohsaka or me. It just waits for its Master's orders.::
5357::$$$message_0045_0046_0028$$$::"Haha. You can't win. My Berserker is the greatest hero of Greece."[lr]::
5358::$$$message_0045_0046_0029$$$::"What!? The greatest hero of Greece? Don't tell me he's[line2]"::
5359::$$$message_0045_0046_0030$$$::"That's right. That demon before you is Heracles.[lr]::
5360::$$$message_0045_0046_0031$$$::He's the most atrocious monster ever, and he's on a different level than any of the heroes you two could summon and handle."::
5361::$$$message_0045_0046_0032$$$::The girl calling herself Illya narrows her eyes in joy.[lr]::
5362::$$$message_0045_0046_0033$$$::Her eyes express elation from the anticipation of finishing off her enemies.::
5363::$$$message_0045_0046_0034$$$::There is no need to ask who she is expecting to kill.[lr]::
5364::$$$message_0045_0046_0035$$$::Saber.[lr]::
5365::$$$message_0045_0046_0036$$$::Then what will I do?[lr]::
5366::$$$message_0045_0046_0037$$$::Am I going to fight that monster instead?[lr]::
5367::$$$message_0045_0046_0038$$$::I can't do that.[lr]::
5368::$$$message_0045_0046_0039$$$::Just getting near that thing without being prepared would be enough to stop my heart.::
5369::$$$message_0045_0046_0040$$$::I'm going to...[lr]::Qí